Africa has recorded 7,778 deaths due to complications arising from COVID-19. According to the latest numbers released by the World Health Organization, WHO, regional office for Africa in Brazzaville, Congo, the number of COVID-19 cases in Africa has risen to 293,721 in the past 24 hours. Africa has also recorded more than 141,000 recoveries from COVID-19 infections. As of Sunday, Egypt has 2,017 reported deaths, the highest on the continent, followed by South Africa with 1,877 fatalities and Algeria with 837. Meanwhile, Africaâ€™s most populous country, Nigeria, has 506 reported deaths.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-807864" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/WHO.jpg" alt="" width="2554" height="1440" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/WHO.jpg 2554w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/WHO-300x169.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/WHO-1024x577.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/WHO-1536x866.jpg 1536w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/WHO-2048x1155.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2554px) 100vw, 2554px">